race.comment: UP AND COMER (5) encouraging return when she shouldered the 60.5kg for a game on pace fourth over 1600m at Orange. Clearly come back well and shapes as a leading player over her preferred trip. VIESTE (7) bounced back to a bit of form with Bradley's 3kg claim when a narrow third over 2000m at Bathurst. Finds a winnable contest despite rising in class. Deep into the prep and goes close. CASINO BEAR (1) tough staying gelding who doesn't know how to run a bad race. Bumped into some handy stayers when running on late to secure fourth over 2000m in the Taree Cup. Placed here and expected to take a hand in the finish. MEGA FIGHT (2) racing in career best form this campaign and had genuine excuses from the outside gate when a dismal ninth over 2000m at Kembla Grange. Assess on earlier efforts.
